Delete Your Crowdwick Data
Crowdwick by Aevon Scientific  ·  Houston, TX

Crowdwick gives you control over your data. You can request deletion of specific types of data without deleting your entire account, or you can delete everything by deleting your account entirely.

Option 1 — Delete specific data (keep your account)
You can remove specific types of data from within the app at any time:

Event decisions (GO / MAYBE / SKIP / Attended)
Profile → Your Plan → remove individual decisions, or they are cleared automatically when you delete your account.
Saved events
Tap the bookmark icon on any saved event to unsave it.
Stories
Stories expire automatically after 24 hours. You can also delete individual stories from your profile.
Group chat messages
You can leave or delete group chats you own. Messages are removed when the chat is deleted.
Profile information
Profile → Edit Profile — update or clear your display name, avatar, and username at any time.
Download your data first
Profile → Download My Data — exports a copy of your data before you delete anything.
Option 2 — Delete everything (delete your account)
To delete all your data permanently, delete your account:

1Open Crowdwick and go to Profile.
2Scroll to the bottom and tap Delete Account.
3Confirm the deletion. All your data will be permanently removed within 30 days.
For full details on what is deleted and what is retained, see the Delete Account page.

Request deletion by email
If you can't access the app, or want to request deletion of a specific data type not listed above, email us at:

crowdwick@gmail.com — include "Data Deletion Request" in the subject line, your account email address, and what data you'd like deleted. We will respond within 30 days.

Retention periods
30 days Personal account data is removed within 30 days of account deletion.
90 days Uploaded media (photos, videos) may remain in backup storage for up to 90 days.
12 months Feedback may be retained in anonymized form for up to 12 months.
Legal holds Certain records may be retained where required by law.
